# Mineflayer Pathfinder

Plugin: [mineflayer-pathfinder](https://www.npmjs.com/package/mineflayer-pathfinder) (npm) · [PrismarineJS/mineflayer-pathfinder](https://github.com/PrismarineJS/mineflayer-pathfinder) (GitHub)

## Install and load

```bash
npm install mineflayer-pathfinder
```

```js
const pathfinder = require('mineflayer-pathfinder').pathfinder;
const Movements = require('mineflayer-pathfinder').Movements;
const { GoalNear, GoalBlock, GoalXZ, GoalFollow } = require('mineflayer-pathfinder').goals;

bot.loadPlugin(pathfinder);
```

## Setup after spawn

Create a `Movements` instance and set it on the pathfinder. Optionally tune costs and behavior (dig, parkour, sprint, etc.).

```js
bot.once('spawn', () => {
  const defaultMove = new Movements(bot);
  // Optional: defaultMove.canDig = false; defaultMove.allow1by1towers = false;
  bot.pathfinder.setMovements(defaultMove);
});
```

## Goals (common)

| Goal | Use case |
|------|----------|
| `GoalBlock(x, y, z)` | Stand inside block at foot level |
| `GoalNear(x, y, z, range)` | Get within `range` blocks of position |
| `GoalXZ(x, z)` | Long-range, any Y |
| `GoalNearXZ(x, z, range)` | Approximate XZ, any Y |
| `GoalGetToBlock(x, y, z)` | Adjacent to block (e.g. chest) |
| `GoalFollow(entity, range)` | Follow an entity |
| `GoalCompositeAny([...])` | Satisfy any one goal |
| `GoalCompositeAll([...])` | Satisfy all goals |

## Setting a goal and moving

```js
// Go to a position (range 1)
bot.pathfinder.setGoal(new GoalNear(x, y, z, 1));

// Async: wait until reached (or error)
await bot.pathfinder.goto(goal);
// Or with dynamic goal (updates when goal moves, e.g. player):
bot.pathfinder.setGoal(new GoalFollow(playerEntity, 2), true);
```

## Pathfinder API (summary)

- `bot.pathfinder.goto(goal)` — returns Promise, resolves when goal reached.
- `bot.pathfinder.setGoal(goal, dynamic?)` — `dynamic: true` for moving targets.
- `bot.pathfinder.setMovements(movements)` — set movement config.
- `bot.pathfinder.stop()` — stop at next node (emits `path_stop`).
- `bot.pathfinder.setGoal(null)` — force stop immediately.
- `bot.pathfinder.isMoving()` / `isMining()` / `isBuilding()` — state checks.
- `bot.pathfinder.bestHarvestTool(block)` — best tool for block (or null).

## Events

- `path_update` — path recalculated; status: `success`, `partial`, `timeout`, `noPath`.
- `goal_reached` — goal reached (not for dynamic goals).
- `path_reset` — path cleared (reason: `goal_updated`, `block_updated`, `stuck`, etc.).
- `path_stop` — stopped via `bot.pathfinder.stop()`.

## Movements options (examples)

- `canDig`, `allow1by1towers`, `allowParkour`, `allowSprinting` — booleans.
- `scafoldingBlocks` — array of item ids for building up.
- `entityIntersections`, `exclusionAreasStep` / `Break` / `Place` — advanced cost/blocking.
